   For a start I would like to point out that some games write the Lives,
  Energy, Money etc to a different address every time the game is loaded, so
  if you find that on loading your game at a later date that nothing happens
  this will be the reason and you will have to start over finding Lives etc.
  Hopefully all the cheats below are set addresses as I haven't checked 
  them all out.
  
   All new additions have been checked twice,so I am sure that these games
  will not write to a different address on reloading.
   
   Mega handshakes to MARK ONEILL for finding Weapons Select and Fist Power
  for Majic Pockets 2 minutes after giving it back to him,maybe now you will
  be able to finish the game after finding the lives hack for yuh!

  Invincibility: How is it done?

  Invincibility is the short flashing shield on your ship when you re-enter
  the game after dying,it's there so on re-entry you are not killed outright.
  
  So how do you count a flashing shield? YOU DON'T!

  First find your lives etc then using the M command go to that
  address, scroll till you have filled the screen then put the lives 
  address in the middle of the screen, print the page out using F5 key.
  Do this when the ship or what ever is not flashing, get yourself
  killed then wait till your ship comes back on the screen, if it's
  flashing go into action replay and back to the monitor using M
  command again, print the screen out as above.
  Now look at both print-outs and find any numbers on the second
  printout that are not on the first and mark them. I have
  found that the address for Invincibility has been in either the
  1st 5 lines above or below the line that the lives is on, so if you
  play around with the numbers that have shown up on the second
  print out you may just find the address for Invincibility.
  I realise this may seem a mickey mouse way of finding a number but
  it works,if you have problems finding it then go back into the
  game and wait till the ship stops flashing and do another printout
  so what you have on paper is flash off, flash on, flash off and this
  may eliminate those other numbers that have popped up in the second
  printout,as I've found a few numbers do pop up in the second sheet.
  You may also find you will need to put a number in the address
  in order to make it work before you TFD the address, as I've done
  with rtype 2 and others.

  CHEATING ON AD&D & ROLEPLAYING:
  -------------------------------

  One of the easiest games to cheat on is the ad&d type game - the
  following on how to do this is the shortest.
  Don't bother to use the trainer commands for this, all you need to
  look for is the characters name by using the FS command
  (SEARCH STRING) E.G let's say your char's name is Warmonger, go into
  Action Replay and type FS "WARMONGER", when the search has stopped 
  you will have possibly 1 or more addresses displayed of where Warmonger 
  was found, go to the first address using the M(monitor) command and scroll
  the full screen,in doing so you should see some other characters who are
  in your party and this is what you are looking for. In some instances
  there are two areas of your chars that are the same, so you will
  need to find out which one works.

  SO WHAT ARE WE LOOKING FOR?

  First write down the stats of your chars (STRENGTH,WISDOM,LUCK)
  and change any over 9 to hex values. You will nearly always find
  these statts just after the char's name and in some cases 2 of the
  same value.E.G
  Warmonger's statts are 9,11,13,10,8,5
  So you should find:
		      09 09 0b 0b 0d 0d 0a 0a 08 08 05 05
                  or  09 0b 0d 0a 08 05
  Change values to what you desire to a max of FF(255),making sure
  that both values are the same.
  You can also find your hit points for each char, but the only
  draw back to this in roll playing games like Curse of the Azure
  Bonds, is that as soon as you rest your party, they change back to
  there original state.To get around this you will need to find the
  experience for your char, put it up to around 16 million and go to
  the guild and boost your char to the max.
  I've played around a lot with ad&d games and have even found all the
  the items that can be found in the game and have even gone to the point
  of adding things to the chars back packs. 
  If you play around a bit you can find a lot of things you wouldn't think
  was possible.

  SOME HINTS ON TIME CLOCKS

  If you are finding it hard to find the address to a clock from a
  game,then move away from the normal search and try something
  different.

  SOME EXAMPLES:
  --------------
  Let's say the clock shows 59.
  You could start your search by looking for the hex value.
		 59 = 3b
  If the address is not found then try the real number.
		    search for 59
  If that also fails then try 0509 or just 509 or  wait till the
  the clock runs down to the last 9 digits and then search. If the
  clock reads 116 then it would look like this E.G 01 01 06.
  
  If all else fails try the search backwards- so if the clock reads 59
  then search for 95 or 0905 etc etc etc

  NOTE 1. NOTE 1. NOTE 1. NOTE 1.
  -------------------------------
  A new addition to time clocks is this.
  If all the above fail try this combination,let's say your clock reads
  45 secs then enter in the search as 34 35 = 45 secs or 150 secs then
  search for 31 35 30.  

  If you are finding it hard to find lives etc for a game then allso try
  using the above method E.G 3 lives search for 33 when the counter goes
  down to 2 then search for 32,you may find that more than one address will
  be found so you'll have to find the one that is the lives address.        
  
  BACKWARDS SEARCHING
  -------------------
  O.K so you can't find those lives,ammo etc etc and you have used every
  combination you can think of-Well how about searching backwards then.
  Lets say your lives counter is 3,lose a life then go into the action
  replay and search for 1(as in 1 life lost) go back to the game and get
  killed again,then search for 2(as in 2 lives lost)get killed again and
  search for 3(as in 3 lives lost).
  This method was used to find MAJIC POCKETS,PINBALL DREAMS/FANTASIES.

  CHECK ALL THOSE NUMBERS
  -----------------------
  Well I've seen some people searching for stuff with the Action Replay and
  wait till the very last entry to have this magical number pop up and to
  there suprise it don't,well stop believing the Action Replay is some Magical
  Device that will find everything for you-if you get 7 addresses after 1st
  entry then print them out cos it may just hold the lives counter and it
  may just not be there at the last entry - so check all your numbers and
  you'll find what you want.

  THE FINAL WORD
  --------------
  YOU WILL HAVE HEARD THAT YOU CAN ONLY DELETE POSITIVE ADDRESSES,THIS IS A
  LOAD OF RUBBISH,YOU WILL FIND THAT YOU CAN DELETE NEGATIVE ADDRESSES AS
  WELL----TO PROVE MY POINT-SEE THE FOLLOWING GAMES
          ARMALYTE
          CELTIC LEGENDS
          MYSTICAL
          VENUS FLY TRAP

