                     CHEATING WITH THE ACTION REPLAY
                     ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ 
                      ON AD&D AND ROLL PLAYING GAMES
                      ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                         BY IAN ELDRIDGE © 1992/93
                         ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                              UPDATED 26/5/93
                              ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                                  PART 1 
                                  ~~~~~~

       BARDSTALE 3
       ~~~~~~~~~~~
       CHARS & CHAR IS SHORT FOR CHARACTERS & CHARACTER
       ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~       
       To find the addresses of your characters,search for the first
       chars name using the FS command.With Bards 3 there is only one
       address,if you are new to the Action Replay then it is easier to
       edit the char with the name to the far left of the screen 
       (Hex side)and as you go along you will be able to scroll through
       the whole char list and edit it from memory.(yours not the computers)

       We'll start on the first char that I loaded.
       NON-MAGIC USER SECTION:
       ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
       NOTE 1.
       ~~~~~~~
       THE FORMAT BELOW NEVER CHANGES,ALL THAT I WILL SHOW STAYS IN THE
       SAME FORMAT ALL THE TIME,THIS IS THE SAME FOR ALL CHARS.THE ONLY
       THING THAT WILL CHANGE WILL BE UNDOCUMENTED BYTES THAT WILL POP
       UP AT SOME TIME DURING PLAY.


LINE 1  49 72 6F 6E 70 61 6E 74 73 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 IRONPANTS.......
LINE 2  13 09 0E 0F 08 00 00 00 07 D0 00 00 00 00 00 02 ................
LINE 3  00 02 00 21 00 21 00 00 00 00 07 02 00 21 00 07 ...!.!.......!..
LINE 4  00 01 03 FF 01 0E FF 01 0A FF 01 11 FF 01 12 FF ................
LINE 5  00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 ................
LINE 6  00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 ................
LINE 7  00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 ................
LINE 8  00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 47 72 65 65 6E 62 ..........GREENB 

       NOTE.............WAIT TILL NIGHT
       ~~~~~
       The line above the 1st char in the list there is 2 ones(01 01) to the
       right of the name, 01 01 is NIGHT 00 00 is DAY,just thought I would
       mention it.

       Where I have LINE 1,LINE 2 etc. is where the address is shown.
       LINE 1.
       ~~~~~~~
       Chars name.(Well that was easy)

       LINE 2.
       ~~~~~~~
       This line has chars statts,experiance,money & level.

LINE 2  13 09 0E 0F 08 00 00 00 07 D0 00 00 00 00 00 02 ................
        ^  ^  ^  ^  ^        ^  ^  ^     ^  ^  ^   ^  ^
        |  |  |  |  |        |  |  |     |  |  |   |  |
       st  iq dx cn lk        experi     m  t  h   level
                                         (money)

        st = stamina                               m = million
        iq = your IQ        experi = experience    t = thousand = money
        dx = dexterity                             h = hundred
        cn = constitution
        lk = luck

        Do not FF (255)all your statts or when you go to the GUILD to
        advance in level they will reset to 0.About AA would do but
        what ever you do put,make sure you leave room for advancement.
        With Experience you will notice I have marked 3 places even 
        though there is only 2 numbers showing ( 07 D0 ).This is because
        your experience starts from D0 and runs backwards when you gain
        more experience.If you FF all 3 addresses you will have over
        16 millions points - the way it works is the same as money above.
        You will have to reset experience if you change class E.G -
        from Magician to Sorcerer.The money value is not yet shown,the 3
        bytes I have shown is where it will be placed,starting from 
        h (hundred) byte.If you wanna change the level of your char then
        the last 2 bytes is for you.

        LINE 3.
        ~~~~~~~
        This line has your Hit points,Class,sex,pic,death & injury bytes,
        & race 
                                            Race
                                           /
LINE 3  00 02 00 21 00 21 00 00 00 00 07 02 00 21 00 07 ...!.!.......!..
              ^  ^  ^  ^               ^     ^  ^  ^
              |  |  |  |              /     /   |   \
              Hit Points           class  sex  pic  death & injury
      
            HIT POINTS
            ~~~~~~~~~~
         Where you see the Two 21 digits is the HIT POINTS,one counts
         down when you are hit and the other stays the same all the time
         and is the most your char can be healed to.The 00 in front of the
         21 is the thousand value of your hit points.Change both values
         to same amount at first E.G - 02 21 02 21 or  00 FF 00 FF

         Note:- If you change 21 to FF(255)(example), when you advance in
         level you will notice that when the counter on the game screen 
         reaches over 999 it will change to *** , just ignore this as the
         onscreen counter will only go to 999,when you look at the HIT
         POINTS in the Action Replay you will notice that they are still
         going up,so don't worry they have not reset to zero.

             CLASS
             ~~~~~
         Bored of the Class of char you are,well change into one of these.
         00 = WARRIOR    01 = WIZARD    02 = SORCERER     03 = CONJURER
         04 = MAGICIAN   05 = ROGUE     06 = BARD         07 = PALADIN
         08 = HUNTER     09 = MONK      0A = ARCHMAGE     
         0B = CHRONOMANCER  0C = GEOMANCER  0D = MONSTER  0E = ILLUSION

             RACE
             ~~~~
         00 = HUMAN  01 = ELF  02 = DWARF  03 = HOBBIT  04 = HALF-ELF
         05 = HALF-ORC  06 = GNOME

              SEX
              ~~~
         Change the sex of your CHAR.
                  00 = MALE    01 = FEMALE
 
              PIC
              ~~~
         So you hate the way you look and you want a change of face,well
         enter a number from 01 to 55 and you can have the pick of 85 new
         images to put in your chars window.              

              DEATH & INJURY
              ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
         So your dead HUH! well just 00 this byte and presto your back in
         the land of the living,just remember to adjust your hit points or
         even if you do change this byte you will stay DEAD,so remember put
         a value in your hit points. 
         This is the same byte for stoned,poisoned,old,paralyzed,nuts
         possessed,just 00 the byte again.
                      some of the values will be. 
                  01 = poisoned  02 = old   03 = poisoned   04 = dead
                  05 = dead      08 = stoned  10 = paralyzed
                  20 = possessed    40 = nuts

         LINE 4.
         ~~~~~~~
         This line has the items to your back pack etc. 

LINE 4  00 01 03 FF 01 0E FF 01 0A FF 01 11 FF 01 12 FF ................
         ^ \  |  /  \  |  /  \  |  /  \  |  /  \  |  /
        /   \ | /    \ | /    \ | /    \ | /    \ | /
       ac  item 1   item 2   item 3   item 4   item 5

         AC
         ~~
         This is your Armour class
         
         ITEMS IN BACKPACK
         ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
         Byte 01 at the start of each item is the EQUIPED or UNEQUIPED
         item byte.In the game it looks like this: -

                  :HELM  
                  ^
                  |
              In the game this is an EQUIPED item(helm being worn)
              or 01 in Action Replay.

                   HELM
                  ^
                  |
               UNEQUIPED item(helm not being worn) or 00 in Action Replay.
          
          You must have 00 or 01 at the start of each item or you get
          funny ASCII codes instead.

          The next byte E.G 03 (item 1 above) is the item byte,in this
          case 03 is a Broadsword .For a full list of Weapons,Armour,Magic
          items,Figurines,and misc items,see the full list below.
          
          Byte FF at the end of each item is the AMOUNT byte as I will
          call it.With a lot of magic items you can cast spells etc.or
          with TNT you have a certain amount to use.E.G
                       
                      HOLY TNT #28   OR   WIZHELM #32


          Byte FF means off.If we put a number in place (up to FE) of FF
          then the item is active (as shown above).Any number including
          FF is for magic items only,make sure you have only FF at the
          end of any non-magic items.The highest number to place is FE
          and doing so will have the same effect as the HIT POINTS. E.G

                      HOLY TNT #**     OR    WIZHELM #**

          The onscreen counter only goes up to 99 and because FE is 254
          the screen will display ** instead.

          LINE 5.
          ~~~~~~~
          Reserved for more items in back pack.

LINE 5  00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 ................          

          You can write up to 12 items in your back pack.

          LINE 6.
          ~~~~~~~
          The 1st 5 bytes reserved for back pack.

LINE 6  00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 ................
        \            /
         end of items

          The rest will be explained in the magic user section.

          MAGIC USER SECTION.
          ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
          
LINE 1  4D 6F 72 67 61 6E 6E 61 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 MORGANNA........
LINE 2  AA AA AA AA AA 00 00 00 FF FF 00 FF FF FF 00 02 .............:..
LINE 3  00 02 00 FF 00 FF 00 15 00 15 03 04 01 4F 00 01 .............O..
LINE 4  00 01 03 FF 01 0E FF 01 0A FF 01 11 FF 01 12 FF ................
LINE 5  00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 ................
LINE 6  00 00 00 00 00 E0 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 ................
LINE 7  00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 ................
LINE 8  00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 52 75 6E 65 66 6C ..........RUNEFL 
         
          Everything in the same format but we'll look at line 3.
          LINE 3.
          ~~~~~~~
          As before we had the HIT POINTS and now MANA POINTS.

LINE 3  00 02 00 FF 00 FF 00 15 00 15 03 04 01 4F 00 01 .............O..
                 ^     ^     ^     ^
                 |     |     |     |
                Hit points  Mana points

          When you change your MANA POINTS and go up in levels,the same
          thing that happens to the HIT POINTS will occur to the MANA
          POINTS.See line 3 in non-magic user section.

          LINE 6.
          ~~~~~~~
          This is where the spells are.
         
LINE 6  00 00 00 00 00 E0 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 ................
        \            / ^
         \          /  |
         end of items  |
                       Start of the spell list.

          E0 is the start of the spell list for 1st level Conjurer,so if
          you want all the spells up to a Archmage (Conjurer,Magician,
          Sorcerer,Wizard,Archmage) then do the following to line 6.

LINE 6  00 00 00 00 00 FF FF FF FF FF FF FF FF FF FE 00 ................ 
                       |                          |
                       |                          |
                         THE COMPLETE SPELL LIST

          When you change to a Chronomancer you lose all your spells from
          all other classes,so the full Chronomancer spell list looks like
          this.

LINE 6  00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 01 F3 ................
                                                  |  |
        __________________________________________|__| 
        |  |
LINE 7  33 33 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 33..............
                        
                        
          The Chronomancer spells end on LINE 7 as shown above,the format
          may be a bit different from THE COMPLETE SPELL LIST but I
          assure you that all spells are shown.
          I have also found out that even though you are a Chronomancer
          you can still put in the other spell list minus FE cos 01 has
          to be there for the Chronomancer.


LINE 7  00 00 3F FF C0 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 ................
               ^  ^  ^
               |  |  |
              GEOMANCER spell list

        The Geomancer can only acquire up to level 7 spells but I found 3
        hidden spells to add to his/her list.
                 They are :-) GILL,DIVA,NUKE
        To get them just put F9 in place of C0 

        ABILITYS
        ~~~~~~~~

LINE 7  00 00 00 00 00 01 02 03 04 05 00 00 00 00 00 00 ................
                        ^  ^  ^  ^  ^
                        |  ----------
                    Bard,hunter,rogue abilitys

           BARD
           ~~~~
          If you are a BARD you only need to use the 1st byte marked 01
          as this is the amount of TUNES you have left to use.
                  09 = 9 tunes etc.

           HUNTER
           ~~~~~~
           If you are a HUNTER you only need to use the 1st byte marked 01
           as this is your CRITICAL HIT ability.                           
                  09 = 3 critical hit
                  03 = 1    "      "

           ROGUE
           ~~~~~
           If you are a ROGUE you need to use all 5 bytes shown 01-05.

           01 = DISARM TRAPS   02 = IDENTIFY CHESTS   03 = IDENTIFY ITEM
           04 = HIDE IN SHADOWS   05 = CRITICAL HIT
                   If you put 09 in the above you will get 3 in that spot.



